Remarks. Material examined shows two forms in the small male specimens, those with a well developed sinus on the male gnathopod 2 posterior margin and those without a sinus. These two phenotypes co-occur in samples and all other characters fit the description of
M. nananui
( sensu stricto ). Ledoyer 1984 also described a non-sinusoidal gnathopod form of
M. nananui
from New Caledonia and the presence of this phenotype at nearby Norfolk Island supports the inclusion of this material.

Mallacoota nananui
was the most frequently sampled benthic amphipod from Norfolk Island during the 2008 collecting expedition.

Distribution.
Australia
. Queensland : Heron Island; One Tree Island. Tasman Sea: Norfolk Island (current study), Lord Howe Island ( Lowry & Springthorpe 2005 ).
